3 (3) (I) “PUBLIC SENIOR HIGHER EDUCATION INSTITUTION”
4 MEANS:
5 1. THE CONSTITUENT INSTITUTIONS OF THE
6 UNIVERSITY SYSTEM OF MARYLAND;
7 2. MORGAN STATE UNIVERSITY; AND
8 3. ST. MARY’S COLLEGE OF MARYLAND.
9 (II) “PUBLIC SENIOR HIGHER EDUCATION INSTITUTION” DOES
10 NOT INCLUDE:
11 1. THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND CENTER FOR
12 ENVIRONMENTAL STUDIES;
13 2. THE UNIVERSITY OF MARYLAND GLOBAL CAMPUS;
14 OR
15 3. THE UNIVERSITY OF BALTIMORE.
16 (B) THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY FINDS THAT ALL STUDENTS AT AN
17 INSTITUTION OF HIGHER EDUCATION IN THE STATE, REGARDLESS OF THEIR
18 GENDER, SHALL ENJOY FREEDOM FROM DISCRIMINATION OF ANY KIND, INCLUDING
19 PREGNANCY DISCRIMINATION AS DESCRIBED IN TITLE IX OF THE EDUCATION
20 AMENDMENTS OF 1972.
21 (C) (1) EACH PUBLIC SENIOR HIGHER EDUCATION INSTITUTION SHALL
22 ADOPT A PLAN REGARDING PREGNANT AND PARENTING STUDENTS THAT IS
23 CONSISTENT WITH TITLE IX OF THE FEDERAL HIGHER EDUCATION ACT.
24 (2) THE PLAN REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
25 SUBSECTION SHALL INCLUDE:
26 (I) REFERRAL TO ON–CAMPUS OR OFF–CAMPUS SERVICES TO
27 ASSIST REGARDING THE AVAILABILITY OF OR ELIGIBILITY FOR GOVERNMENT
28 ASSISTANCE PROGRAMS, INCLUDING:
29 1. THE SPECIAL SUPPLEMENTAL NUTRITION
30 ASSISTANCE PROGRAM FOR WOMEN, INFANTS, AND CHILDREN;

